25/03/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- In a bid to streamline the cabinet, the government has decided to make Minister without Portfolio Bianka Matkovic a state secretary in the economy ministry, Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor announced on Wednesday (March 24th).
Matkovic had been mentioned in a possible cabinet reshuffle as early as January.
A close ally of former Prime Minister Ivo Sanader, her new duties as state secretary for economic diplomacy will be to work on advancing long stalled projects.
(HRT, Javno, Novi List - 24/03/10)
